{"TopicId":137830,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.9.x] Mouse Aim Flight (1.1.3) - Pilot airplanes with your mouse!","CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-23T07:17:49Z","PageNum":10,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Osel","CreatedById":149834,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-15T08:05:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223415158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531522071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/14/2018 at 12:47 AM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea why my mod is on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E at all, I never allowed that in the first place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022blink.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002220\u0022 src=\u0022http://bsc.it-services.sk/bceny/blink.gif\u0022 width=\u002220\u0022\u003E ...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022awcrap.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002220\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.biosector.sk/chat/awcrap.gif\u0022 width=\u002225\u0022\u003E\u00A0...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022shakehead.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002215\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.biosector.sk/chat/shakehead.gif\u0022 width=\u002215\u0022\u003E\u00A0...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223415769\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531622711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... if you dont want it on\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN ...\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022crybaby.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022104\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.sherv.net/cm/emo/sad/crybaby.gif\u0022 width=\u0022120\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-15T11:43:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222532887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461395869\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/23/2016 at 3:17 AM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EChangelog:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\n\nv1.1.2\nPorted to KSP 1.3\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250204\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tetryds\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTwo things:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst, the recommended convention on the forums is to keep the title of the thread updated with the latest version the mod is available for. The title says 1.2.1, yet it seems you updated it for 1.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSecond, and this is a personal recommendation, for something like this, which interacts with the game mechanics, I personally prefer to have a recomiled version for each major version of KSP.\u00A0 Because of this, I can\u0027t even consider trying this mod on 1.4\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Papa_Joe","CreatedById":10788,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-17T18:42:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe BDAc team has reached out to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250204\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tetryds\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 to inquire about assuming\u00A0support for this mod.\u00A0 Given that portions of the code are based on BDA, and the fact that we are now maintaining a range of BDA based mods\u00A0with permission, it makes sense that we should assume continuing support.\u00A0 As soon as we hear back from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250204\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tetryds\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(assuming he approves) we will be releasing a KSP 1.4.x compatible version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-17T19:32:29Z\u0022 title=\u002207/17/2018 07:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 17, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Papa_Joe\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"se5a","CreatedById":156245,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-22T06:12:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223417151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531852944\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210788\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Papa_Joe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/18/2018 at 6:42 AM, Papa_Joe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe BDAc team has reached out to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250204\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tetryds\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 to inquire about assuming\u00A0support for this mod.\u00A0 Given that portions of the code are based on BDA, and the fact that we are now maintaining a range of BDA based mods\u00A0with permission, it makes sense that we should assume continuing support.\u00A0 As soon as we hear back from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002250204\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/50204-tetryds/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tetryds\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(assuming he approves) we will be releasing a KSP 1.4.x compatible version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027d be great. I\u0027ve just started getting back into KSP after a year and I\u0027m missing this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"doxlulzem","CreatedById":153306,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-31T23:37:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s 1.4 that\u0027s causing it, but when I use MAF now, my plane rolls from side to side constantly and increasingly severe. I don\u0027t recall it ever being an issue before, and it certainly doesn\u0027t do it with regular control, and obviously I can\u0027t use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to prevent it, so I\u0027m at a loss. Has anyone experienced this and can name a solution, or do I have to wait and hope that the BDAc team pick it up and release a 1.4 compatible version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shoryuken","CreatedById":191176,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-18T15:52:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223425468\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221533080277\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153306\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022doxlulzem\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/1/2018 at 1:37 AM, doxlulzem said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s 1.4 that\u0027s causing it, but when I use MAF now, my plane rolls from side to side constantly and increasingly severe. I don\u0027t recall it ever being an issue before, and it certainly doesn\u0027t do it with regular control, and obviously I can\u0027t use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to prevent it, so I\u0027m at a loss. Has anyone experienced this and can name a solution, or do I have to wait and hope that the BDAc team pick it up and release a 1.4 compatible version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndid you came up with something ??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T13:14:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really no good at flying without this. Stock controlls are too jittery and joysticks aren\u0027t my jive. Is there any other mod I can use for mouse controlled flight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-28T08:41:47Z\u0022 title=\u002209/28/2018 08:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tricky14\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jacke","CreatedById":103694,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T13:41:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223456992\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537794853\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145768\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tricky14\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, Tricky14 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really no good at flying without this. Stock controlls are to jittery and joysticks aren\u0027t my jive. Is there any other mod I can use for mouse controlled flight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a couple options in stock KSP and another mod that might help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPress the Caps-Lock key to toggle precision controls on and off.\u00A0 Instead of your WSADQE key presses immediately forcing the pitch, yaw, and/or roll to maximum, they\u0027ll slowly ramp up, allowing short key-presses for fine adjustment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also trim controls on all three axes, pitch, yaw, roll.\u00A0 Trim shifts the zero point of the controls away from its default (control surfaces in default positions).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApply trim by using the [Mod] key (on Windows it\u0027s the Alt key) with the WSADQE keys.\u00A0\u00A0 From the KSP Wiki\u0027s article on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Key_bindings\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKey bindings\u003C/a\u003E:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ctable style=\u0022height:49px;\u0022 width=\u0022364\u0022\u003E\u003Ctbody\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd\u003E\nMod \u002B W/S/A/D/Q/E\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\nTrim pitch/yaw/roll\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.15.0\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd\u003E\nMod \u002B X\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\nReset trim\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd\u003E\n0.15.0\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/tbody\u003E\u003C/table\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nTrim really only needs to be used with pitch (Mod\u002BS, Mod\u002BW, Mod\u002BX) to maintain level flight.\u00A0 Mod\u002BS pulls back on the stick until the aircraft is either flying level or ascending or descending at about the rate desired.\u00A0 Mod\u002BW to reduce the pitch trim and Mod\u002BX to reset trim if needed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s also the mod TAC Sticky Controls that acts like trim.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3075809358\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164129-141-tac-sticky-controls/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-09-24T13:43:22Z\u0022 title=\u002209/24/2018 01:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Jacke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JH4C","CreatedById":188049,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T14:12:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223456992\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537794853\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145768\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tricky14\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Tricky14 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really no good at flying without this. Stock controlls are to jittery and joysticks aren\u0027t my jive. Is there any other mod I can use for mouse controlled flight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAtmosphere Autopilot also offers a mouse-yoke option, but I\u0027ve not used it or this mod so I can offer no comparison.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6832901930\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/124417-122-145-dlc-atmosphereautopilot-1511-looking-for-maintainer/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-24T23:55:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457005\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537796511\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jacke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Jacke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPress the Caps-Lock key to toggle precision controls on and off.\u00A0 Instead of your WSADQE key presses immediately forcing the pitch, yaw, and/or roll to maximum, they\u0027ll slowly ramp up, allowing short key-presses for fine adjustment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not know you could do that. I\u0027m not sure if I can do enough with that to fly, but I\u0027ll certainly give it a fair shot. Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223457021\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537798333\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188049\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JH4C\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, JH4C said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAtmosphere Autopilot also offers a mouse-yoke option, but I\u0027ve not used it or this mod so I can offer no comparison.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4927471645\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/124417-122-145-dlc-atmosphereautopilot-1511-looking-for-maintainer/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hadn\u0027t heard of that, I\u0027ll check it out. Thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-29T15:50:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223456992\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221537794853\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145768\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tricky14\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/24/2018 at 10:14 AM, Tricky14 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m really no good at flying without this. Stock controlls are too jittery and joysticks aren\u0027t my jive. Is there any other mod I can use for mouse controlled flight?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs MAF not working on the latest version of KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tricky14","CreatedById":145768,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-01T18:58:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, it\u0027s working again. I ran the game with some serious mod conflicts for a while without realizing it. Fixed all that now, MAF is fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bitrefresh","CreatedById":146227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T05:02:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223459711\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221538236206\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/30/2018 at 12:50 AM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs MAF not working on the latest version of KSP?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnope. not really. a recompile for 1.4 and 1.5 would be really nice.. I\u0027m trying to dogfight a MiG-21 with guns in an F-35, and I can\u0027t really do anything because his aim is too good.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T21:03:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485703\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541998939\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bitrefresh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Bitrefresh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnope. not really. a recompile for 1.4 and 1.5 would be really nice.. I\u0027m trying to dogfight a MiG-21 with guns in an F-35, and I can\u0027t really do anything because his aim is too good.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it not working at all or is it not working \u0022well\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause that may be more about your craft. If the mouse flight works, its working as it should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it simply does not work then it needs a recompile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bitrefresh","CreatedById":146227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T22:58:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223486060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542056608\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it not working at all or is it not working \u0022well\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBecause that may be more about your craft. If \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ethe mouse flight works, its working as it should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it simply does not work then it needs a recompile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI shouldve been more clear. Trying to dogfight a MiG-21 is next to impossible when you cant aim with the mouse. the mod doesnt seem to work. I\u0027ll clear my KSP gamedata and try again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bitrefresh","CreatedById":146227,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-14T02:39:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright update, after reinstalling all of my mods along with MAF, it does work. and it works relatively well at that. Sorry for the trouble or confusion. o7.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-15T02:26:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223486921\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542163184\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bitrefresh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Bitrefresh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright update, after reinstalling all of my mods along with MAF, it does work. and it works relatively well at that. Sorry for the trouble or confusion. o7.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problem, just checking if it \u0022actually works at all\u0022. In case it does not I will do at least the bare minimum to keep it alive, that\u0027s for sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Modding Maniac","CreatedById":186729,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-19T15:04:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo im guessing this mod is dead\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T01:53:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223525022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547910281\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186729\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Modding Maniac\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/19/2019 at 1:04 PM, Modding Maniac said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo im guessing this mod is dead\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, just like I mentioned earlier, if it needs a recompile or anything\u00A0just let me know and I\u0027ll keep it working \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-23T01:53:23Z\u0022 title=\u002201/23/2019 01:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 23, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by tetryds\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Modding Maniac","CreatedById":186729,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T12:17:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548208392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, just like I mentioned earlier, if it needs a recompile or anything\u00A0just let me know and I\u0027ll keep it working \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noh! thats awsome!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sticky3002","CreatedById":190350,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-28T21:30:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527203\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548208392\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250204\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tetryds\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/22/2019 at 10:53 PM, tetryds said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, just like I mentioned earlier, if it needs a recompile or anything\u00A0just let me know and I\u0027ll keep it working \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be very much appreciated. The stability and maneuverablity is kind of choppy in the newer versions of KSP. Flight isn\u0027t as smooth and enjoyable as other videos I\u0027ve seen in older versions\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T05:00:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223549098\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551389429\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190350\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sticky3002\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/28/2019 at 6:30 PM, Sticky3002 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be very much appreciated. The stability and maneuverablity is kind of choppy in the newer versions of KSP. Flight isn\u0027t as smooth and enjoyable as other videos I\u0027ve seen in older versions\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have way too much control, much more than you need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, try using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E, will work much better with it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jrolson","CreatedById":77793,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-29T18:17:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill works in 1.7 but the roll is too sensitive on planes and you get a bad wobble.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA simple fix for this is to remove roll functions on some of your rudders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tetryds","CreatedById":50204,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-04-30T17:50:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223591143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022137830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221556561857\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277793\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022jrolson\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, jrolson said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill works in 1.7 but the roll is too sensitive on planes and you get a bad wobble.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA simple fix for this is to remove roll functions on some of your rudders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you probably have very short wings, which makes your airplane very roll-happy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGlad that you figured out a way to adapt your aircraft to use MAF \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Miracle Magician","CreatedById":197080,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-02T03:40:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I started using this mod I just simply found something isn\u0027t right about this mod, until I accidentially found this: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/brihernandez/MouseFlight\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/brihernandez/MouseFlight\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems that to get the feelings right when controlling an aircraft using mouse, your camera should always follow the mouse position with a slight delay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd then I did some small modification to your code, and then got this result:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/-Yk-xZEogJ8?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(youtube decided my video can\u0027t have 1080p so sorry for that video quality...)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI feel the control got way more natual since I don\u0027t need to move my camera postion, and should really be a part of the mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever since my major isn\u0027t CS and I only learned a little programming by myself, so the modification is really sluggish and I don\u0027t think they are good enough to open a pull request on github. What should I do now?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-05-02T04:24:24Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2019 04:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Miracle Magician\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}